Tags.ImageDescription: A view down Moy Avenue, older two-storey homes with large, leafy trees. This, to me, is classic Ontario. This is what I grew up with and I miss it where I live now, as we don't have much of this sort of thing in Calgary. Even more so, looking down the end sends you across the St. Clair River into Detroit; looking from one neighbourhood into the United States isn't too common in Canada, despite our long border.
